data.text: @LightShedder85 @msdh I'm not here to argue either. I'm just saying the chart you posted does not mean the vaxxed are more likely to die.

@1ReganTaylor @msdh Exactly. You get the jab and you’re more likely to be included in that number. You don’t get it and you’re 100% free of “death” as an adverse event (listed in official FDA dox for the vaccines). I’m not here to argue so we may have to agree to disagree. Have a good one!
@LightShedder85 @msdh Well the closer the vax rate is to 100% the more likely it is that the vaxxed deaths will be 100% and it doesn't mean there's anything wrong with the vaccine.
@BrianSMoore3 @msdh Here’s Brian right on time to try to convince us not to care about people dying!!!
@1ReganTaylor @msdh I def see what you’re saying. But England has a very high vaccination rate…between 80-97% in nearly all eligible age groups. https://t.co/q4aTgWjTKt

@chriskbell1 @msdh Are you talking about totals for the entire pandemic, or just the 61 reported today?  If it is the 61 number then it is because the reports go all the way back to November.  MSDH has a chart showing deaths by actual date here which is much lower:

https://t.co/OqESez2N2f
